   <p><placeName ref="cwgk:P00000537">Carlisle</placeName>, <placeName ref="cwgk:P001800">Ky</placeName>,
<lb/><date when="1861-09-17">Sep 17 1861</date>
    <lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00000258">Hon B, Magoffin</persName>,</p>
<p>Sir, Our friend <persName ref="cwgk:N00007494">W<hi rend="sup">m</hi> Still</persName> became security upon a replevin bond for <persName ref="cwgk:N00007476">Michel Burns</persName>, who was fined at the last term of the <orgName ref="cwgk:O00000477">Nicholas Circuit Court</orgName> $50, for carrying concealed deadly weapons, Since the bond was given Burns has died ^without any means or property,^ and M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Still now asks that the amount thereof may be remitted. I respectfully unite in that request and ask that M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Still may be released, and the amount of the bond remitted,</p>
<p>Respectfully, 
<lb/>Your Obt Svt 
 <lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00002605">R H Stanton</persName></p>
<p>We, citizens of <placeName ref="cwgk:P00000539">Nicholas County</placeName>, recommend to the Governor, the propriety of remitting the above. <date when="1861-09-18">Sept. 18, 1861.</date></p>
